    Oysters Rockefeller

    Oysters Rockefeller is a dish consisting of oysters topped with a rich mixture of herbs, breadcrumbs, butter, and other ingredients, then baked or broiled until bubbling and golden.

    Lobster Thermidor

    Lobster meat cooked in a creamy sauce with white wine, egg yolks, and cheese, then typically stuffed back into the lobster shell and baked.

    • Country : France
    • History : 19 century

    Fish and Chips

    Fish and chips is a classic British dish consisting of battered and deep-fried fish (typically cod or haddock) served with thick-cut fries (chips). It is often accompanied by malt vinegar, salt, and tartar sauce.

    • Country : United Kingdom
    • History : Britain
    • weight : 4 kg
